article.headline: Michigan 68, Northwestern 51
article.story: ANN ARBOR, Mich. (AP) -- Lester Abram scored 20 and Dion Harris had 15 points to lead Michigan past Northwestern 68-51 Wednesday night. The Wolverines (12-3, 2-2 Big Ten) broke open a close game with 11 straight points from late in the first half to early in the second. Wildcats reserve Mohamed Hachad scored 17 and Vedran Vukusic scored just two of his 15 points in the second half. The Wildcats (9-7, 2-3) have lost three straight Big Ten games after starting 2-0 in the conference for the first time in 23 years. While Michigan was ahead by 22 midway through the second half, point guard Daniel Horton fell to the ground and held his left ankle. He limped off the floor but was later able to run down the tunnel and return to the bench. Horton finished with four points and eight assists. The Wolverines built their first cushion with a 10-0 run, taking a 17-9 lead midway through the first half. After Northwestern pulled within three, the Wolverines responded with an 11-4 run to go ahead 30-20. Brent Petway's back-to-back dunks put Michigan ahead 38-31 at halftime, and it led by 14 after the game's decisive run. The Wolverines were able to coast the rest of the way.
